    "summary": "This website is designed to help identify plants found growing wild in South Dakota and to promote the use of native species in urban and rural landscapes. The plants on this website are arranged by form: 1. non-flowering, non-seed producing plants (ferns and horsetails), 2. Flowering herbaceous species, 3. Grasses, sedges and rushes, and 4. Trees, shrubs and woody vines. Each section has the families arranged alphabetically. Each entry describes a plant and provides information on its uses and, if it is a native species, information on how to collect seeds and propagate the plant for your personal use. This entry also includes aids to identifying the families of flowering herbaceous plants and the genera of Asteraceae (the sunflower family). In addition, there are entries defining some of"
